<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2015/06/nuspec.xsd">
  <metadata>
    <id>kc</id>
    <version>0.0.11</version>
    <title>kc </title>
    <authors>riezebosch</authors>
    <tags>kc admin revealjs nodejs presentation</tags>
    <summary>Installeert de tools om presentaties te maken met Reveal.js</summary>
    <description>
## nieuwe presentaties:

* Open Visual Studio Code
* Open de folder waarin je een presentatie wilt maken
* Open de integrated terminal (waarschijnlijk met CTRL+')
* kc serve
* Watch and learn

## voor bestaande presentaties:
​
* Clone vanaf gitlab https://gitlab.rhea.infosupport.net/kenniscentrum/
* Open Visual Studio Code (rechtermuisknop op de folder)
* Open de integrated terminal
* kc serve

    </description>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency id="nodejs" version="7.7.3" />
      <dependency id="visualstudiocode" version="1.0.0" />
      <dependency id="git.install" version="2.5.0" />
    </dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <!-- this section controls what actually gets packaged into the Chocolatey package -->
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
    <!--Building from Linux? You may need this instead: <file src="tools/**" target="tools" />-->
  </files>
</package>
